name: Agrios
holysymbol: A 7-pointed star with each point a different color
domains: Goddess of the Feywind, Wild places, freedom, and raw emotion.
worshippers: Fey creatures and many elves, particularly wild elves.
appearance: Agrios appears as a fairy, constantly in motion, with rainbow hair and a dress that is constantly changing colors.
tenets: There is a healing power to laughter
Jealously guard your freedom, it is worth more than your life
The wild places are holy, they reflect the truths of the world
Always be sure to do more good than harm
Do not hide your emotions, be honest with others in how you feel
parents: 3rd Generation, born of Sylvan and Gaian
lore: Agrios, as the child of the two elder nature Gods, has followed in their footsteps. Yet where Gaian is the high lord of the material plane, representative of the natural order, and Sylvan is the God of winds and animals, and nature in service of man, Agrios represents nature gone wild, the world overgrown, and emotions unchecked.
